<body background="../../bkgrnd2.gif">
 <keyword><date>1871</date> <date>1872</date><type>Lecture 1871-72</type> <country>American</country> <regions>Eastern</regions> <opinion>Unfavorable</opinion></keyword>
<center><h2><i>The (Allentown) Daily Chronicle</i></h2></center>
<center><b>1871: October 18</b></center>
<br>
<table align="center" width=400 border=0 cellpadding=0>
<tr><td>

<p>W<font size=-1>E</font> were favored, yesterday, by a visit from Mark Twain, and were surprised to find him similar to other people and not at all inclined to throw his wit around loose.  He evidently considered it very precious and he has good cause for doing so, considering the price it brings.</p>
</td></tr></table><br>

<a href="7172schd.html"><img src="../../barrel.jpg" align="left"></a>
